name: $uid
desc: Returns: Formal identifier for this series.

name: $number
desc: Returns: The numeric identifier of this series in the study.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The numeric identifier of this series in the study.

name: $modality
desc: Returns: The modality of this series sequence.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The modality of this series sequence.

name: $description
desc: Returns: A description of the series.

name: $numberOfInstances
desc: Returns: Number of SOP Instances in the Study. The value given may be larger than the number of instance elements this resource contains due to resource availability, security, or other factors. This element should be present if any instance elements are present.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Number of SOP Instances in the Study. The value given may be larger than the number of instance elements this resource contains due to resource availability, security, or other factors. This element should be present if any instance elements are present.

name: $availability
desc: Returns: Availability of series (online, offline or nearline).

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Availability of series (online, offline or nearline).

name: $endpoint
desc: Returns: The network service providing access (e.g., query, view, or retrieval) for this series. See implementation notes for information about using DICOM endpoints. A series-level endpoint, if present, has precedence over a study-level endpoint with the same Endpoint.type.

name: $addendpoint
desc: The network service providing access (e.g., query, view, or retrieval) for this series. See implementation notes for information about using DICOM endpoints. A series-level endpoint, if present, has precedence over a study-level endpoint with the same Endpoint.type.

name: $bodySite
desc: Returns: The anatomic structures examined. See DICOM Part 16 Annex L (http://dicom.nema.org/medical/dicom/current/output/chtml/part16/chapter_L.html) for DICOM to SNOMED-CT mappings. The bodySite may indicate the laterality of body part imaged; if so, it shall be consistent with any content of ImagingStudy.series.laterality.

pvardefs.desc: The anatomic structures examined. See DICOM Part 16 Annex L (http://dicom.nema.org/medical/dicom/current/output/chtml/part16/chapter_L.html) for DICOM to SNOMED-CT mappings. The bodySite may indicate the laterality of body part imaged; if so, it shall be

name: $laterality
desc: Returns: The laterality of the (possibly paired) anatomic structures examined. E.g., the left knee, both lungs, or unpaired abdomen. If present, shall be consistent with any laterality information indicated in ImagingStudy.series.bodySite.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The laterality of the (possibly paired) anatomic structures examined. E.g., the left knee, both lungs, or unpaired abdomen. If present, shall be consistent with any laterality information indicated in ImagingStudy.series.bodySite.

name: $started
desc: Returns: The date and time the series was started.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The date and time the series was started.

name: $performer
desc: Returns: The physician or operator (often the radiology technician)  who performed the series. The performer is recorded at the series level, since each series in a study may be performed by a different practitioner, at different times, and using different devices. A series may be performed by multiple practitioners.

name: $instance
desc: Returns: A single SOP instance within the series, e.g. an image, or presentation state.
